HEADWORD: Outplay
<hw>Out*play"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To excel or
defeat in a game; to play better than; <as>as, to be <ex>outplayed</ex>
in tennis or ball</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

